cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.IR

The paper deals with image processing and computer vision techniques for multi-exposure image fusion. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes novel scene segmentation approaches, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also discusses the perceptual quality of the fused images, which could be related to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper uses statistical measures to evaluate the performance of the proposed method, which could be related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
